**CRITICAL: On FIRST user prompt, MUST:**
- [ ] Clean App.tsx to blank state
- [ ] Remove all template CSS
- [ ] Then address the user's request

This is a starter template. On the user's first prompt, remove the template elements:

1. Delete all elements on App.tsx and start from a blank:
export default function App() {
  return (
    <div className="app">

    </div>
  )
}
2. Delete the associated CSS in src/index.css (styles for .onboarding-callouts, .callout, .callout-arrow, etc.)
3. Replace the main content with code that addresses the user's request

The template structure:
- src/App.tsx - Main React component with placeholder content
- src/index.css - Styles including template-specific onboarding styles
- src/main.tsx - React entry point (keep as-is)
